<li><a href="http://books.guardian.co.uk/reviews/biography/0,,1826088,00.html" class="external text" title="http://books.guardian.co.uk/reviews/biography/0,,1826088,00.html" rel="nofollow">Donne undone: Review of "John Donne: The Reformed Soul"(John Stubbs)</a>, <a href="/wiki/Guardian_Unlimited" title="Guardian Unlimited" class="mw-redirect">Guardian Unlimited</a>, July 22, 2006, by Andrew Motion.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.poetseers.org/the_great_poets/british_poets/john_donne/john_donne_poems/" class="external text" title="http://www.poetseers.org/the_great_poets/british_poets/john_donne/john_donne_poems/" rel="nofollow">Selected Poems of John Donne</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.lib.byu.edu/dlib/donne/" class="external text" title="http://www.lib.byu.edu/dlib/donne/" rel="nofollow">Complete sermons of John Donne</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.sparknotes.com/poetry/donne/" class="external text" title="http://www.sparknotes.com/poetry/donne/" rel="nofollow">John Donne: Sparknotes</a></li>
<li><a href="http://donnevariorum.tamu.edu/" class="external text" title="http://donnevariorum.tamu.edu/" rel="nofollow">The Donne Variorum</a></li>
<li><a href="http://digitaldonne.tamu.edu/" class="external text" title="http://digitaldonne.tamu.edu/" rel="nofollow">Digital Donne (digital images of early Donne editions and manuscripts)</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.literaryescorts.com/?act=non-fiction&amp;item=548" class="external text" title="http://www.literaryescorts.com/?act=non-fiction&amp;item=548" rel="nofollow">An essay on Donne's "The Bait"</a> exploring buried sexual imagery</li>
</ul>
